From: Fancy Fang <chen.fang@nxp.com>
Date: Fri, 8 Jul 2016 15:30:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 51/85] MLK-12975-2 video: mxsfb: missing a 'break' in the
 case statement.

Missing the 'break' will cause the function return failure
when the 'bits_per_pixel' is 32 which should be supported.

Signed-off-by: Fancy Fang <chen.fang@nxp.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.freescale.com/imx/linux-imx.git imx_4.1.15_2.0.0_ga]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
index 740e0b2..5618ac3 100644
--- a/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
+++ b/drivers/video/fbdev/mxsfb.c
@@ -1043,6 +1043,7 @@ static int mxsfb_restore_mode(struct mxsfb_info *host)
 		break;
 	case 3:
 		bits_per_pixel = 32;
+		break;
 	case 1:
 	default:
 		return -EINVAL;
